President Barack Obama has announced his intent to appoint two individuals to key administration posts. Glenn S. Gerstell is set to become a member of the National Infrastructure Advisory Commission. He is currently the Managing Partner of the law firm Milbank, Tweed, Hadley & McCloy LLP in Washington, D.C. Charles "Chip" Lyons is set to become the United States Alternate Representative to the Executive Board on the United Nations Children’s Fund (UNICEF). He is currently the President and Chief Executive Officer of the Elizabeth Glaser Pediatric AIDS Foundation. Prior to this, he worked for the United Nations Children’s Fund (UNICEF) and the Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation.